events.description: The Reserve Bank of Australia lifted interest rates by 25 basis points to 3.85%.
Governor Michele Bullock spoke to lawmakers regarding inflation risks and demand growth.

facts.fact_text: The Reserve Bank of Australia lifted interest rates by 25bps to 3.85%.

evidences.evidence_text: The central bank lifted rates by 25bps to 3.85% after inflation reaccelerated following three cuts last year.

facts.fact_text: Underlying inflation rose to 3.4% in Q4.

evidences.evidence_text: Underlying inflation rose to 3.4% in Q4, the highest in over a year

facts.fact_text: Consumer prices have exceeded forecasts for two consecutive quarters.

evidences.evidence_text: Consumer prices have exceeded forecasts for two straight quarters, staying well above the 2%–3% target.
